=====================================
          FULL ARC DATA LIST
=====================================


 ARC DATA ELEMENT       | CONTEXT / RELAY TO ENGINE
------------------------|--------------------------------------------
 Bind-2-action          | [event/entity/object {action}]: set special stuff to activate upon an action
 Bind-2-event           | {action/entity/object [event]}: set special stuff to activate upon an event
 Bind-2-entity          | (event/action/object (entity)): set special stuff to activate upon an entity
 $imported map#         | a needed map for this arc, use the map import header for more
 $generate map!         | a needed map to be generated on the fly
 ***Starting Text***    | triggers at arc start; info/lore; use arrows for multi-page (book animation)
 'monster names'        | types of known or wanted monsters to spawn
 ~object drops~         | objects expected to drop
 drop%                  | percentage at which things drop (follows monster/object or generic rate)
 +spawn_rates           | percentage at which things spawn (follows monster/object or generic rate)
 ^interactable event^   | allowed interactable events (trigger on exit if no objects)
 *mandatory event*      | forced interactable events (trigger on entry if no objects)
 /User's Thoughts/      | text for user's character thinking
 \User's Speech\        | text for user's character speaking
 _Noticed actions_      | text describing what happened or was seen
 -NPC Speech-           | text for NPC or non-user-playable-character speaking
 ->'CHARACTER_NAME'     | pointer to addressed character (after thought/speech/action)
 ->data_phrase          | pointer to addressed via data phrase (after thought/speech/action)
 <-                     | back action arrow: points to effected for what comes after (instant)
 ->                     | front action arrow: points to effected for what comes before (instant)
 <<                     | back effect arrows: points to targeted for what comes after (may linger)
 >>                     | front effect arrows: points to targeted for what comes before (may linger)
 ***Completion Text***  | appears on goal complete or arc end

=====================================
  Use for story, events, integrations.
  See phrases for triggers; waypoints ('Q'/'I') link via symbols.
=====================================
